&lt;p&gt;Datadog’s Finance team collaborates with teams across the organization, providing commercial, operational, and analytical support to ensure that Datadog’s business continues to grow as rapidly and efficiently as possible.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a Billing Operations Analyst to join our growing Finance team at Datadog. As a member of the Billing Operations team, you will serve as a trusted partner within the Finance organization, delivering support to a wide range of internal departments and external customers. In this role, you will play a meaningful part in key initiatives designed to drive operational efficiency and create lasting impact across multiple teams and stakeholders.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;What You&#39;ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage multiple internal tools and systems to research, analyze, and resolve complex billing questions and customer inquiries.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with cross-functional teams—including Customer Success, Sales, DealDesk, Sales Systems, Order Operations, and Product—to provide support and insights into Datadog’s billing practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help customers understand their invoices and billing details, which vary based on usage patterns and plan type.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively identify, communicate, and collaborate with the Customer Success and Sales teams to resolve customer billing discrepancies and issues in a timely manner.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and triage an incoming queue of requests and inquiries across Zendesk, Jira, and a dedicated Billing Operations Slack channel, ensuring prompt and accurate responses.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to ad-hoc projects and process improvement initiatives as they arise.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Accounting, Finance, or Computer Science.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1–3 years of relevant professional work experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in Google Sheets and/or Microsoft Excel.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and verbal communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactive, hands-on approach with a passion for tackling new challenges and continuously improving existing processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong attention to detail with the ability to effectively multi-task and prioritize in a fast-paced environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bonus Points:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior experience in a SaaS environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience with NetSuite and/or Salesforce.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working knowledge of SQL.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with data visualization tools such as Tableau and/or Metabase.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
